1. install depencies-  download epel repo && install the epel repo && install packages (git, ansible, python, python-pip,)
2. install ansible
2. create user and password -useradd
4. navigate suders file ( visudo) to add user under root ( ansiadmin ALL=(ALL) PASSWD: ALL 
5. now the user can use (sudo to run commands)
6. navigate sshd confi file ( vi /etc/ssh/ssh_config) to change password authentication to "yes" from "no"
7. the user( ansiadmi) will be able to connect to other machines via ssh

